WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.961
VICTOR: Here you go.
CUSTOMER: Thank you.

00:02.961 --> 00:04.588
‐ Sorry I’m late.

00:04.588 --> 00:06.757
I had that dream again
where the Hemsworth brothers

00:06.757 --> 00:08.258
teach me how to surf.
‐ Mmm.

00:08.258 --> 00:10.010
‐ Still holding out hope
that it’s a premonition.

00:10.010 --> 00:12.596
‐ [chuckles] Well, lucky for you,

00:12.596 --> 00:15.182
today’s the only day
you’re allowed to be late.

00:15.182 --> 00:16.558
Happy birthday.

00:16.558 --> 00:17.976
[laughs]

00:17.976 --> 00:21.605
And I’m glad you slept in,
'cause I can't have you tired for tonight.

00:21.605 --> 00:22.940
I have big plans for us.

00:22.940 --> 00:24.650
‐ Oh, yeah? What kind of plans?

00:24.650 --> 00:27.694
‐ Uh, let's just say I may have "borrowed"

00:27.694 --> 00:30.072
a bottle of champagne from
my mom's wine cabinet.

00:30.072 --> 00:32.908
A little bit of drinking,
a little bit of fooling around.

00:32.908 --> 00:35.619
And that’s all I have planned.
Should I have tried a little bit harder?

00:35.619 --> 00:37.454
‐ No. No, that's perfect.

00:37.454 --> 00:41.083
My parents should be out cold after this
bougie dinner they’re dragging me to.

00:41.083 --> 00:42.459
‐ I'm sure it won't be that bad.

00:42.459 --> 00:44.878
‐ You haven’t heard my mom
try and impress a French waiter

00:44.878 --> 00:46.630
with her pronunciation of ratatouille.

00:46.630 --> 00:48.632
[laughs]
[door opens]

00:48.632 --> 00:50.884
Oh, wow. I accidentally summoned her.

00:50.884 --> 00:52.427
‐ Hi, boys.

00:52.427 --> 00:54.263
‐ Hey.
‐ Ooh!

00:54.263 --> 00:56.265
Said it before and I’ll say it again,

00:56.265 --> 00:58.892
the softest cheeks in Creekwood.

00:58.892 --> 01:01.645
Can you believe this sneaky cat
left the house

01:01.645 --> 01:04.398
without letting his own mother
wish him a happy birthday?

01:04.398 --> 01:06.191
Happy birthday, darling.

01:06.191 --> 01:08.777
It’s a pain au chocolat from Café Jacquot.

01:08.777 --> 01:12.030
‐ Odd gift, considering I’m surrounded
by pastries all day.

01:12.030 --> 01:15.284
But it's very sweet. Thank you, Mom.
MARGARET: Mmm.

01:15.284 --> 01:16.577
Oh, Benji, before I go,

01:16.577 --> 01:19.746
could you make me one of those
delicious oat milk lattes?

01:19.746 --> 01:21.999
‐ Sure, Mother.
[Victor chuckles]

01:22.833 --> 01:24.585
‐ Okay. The coast is clear.

01:24.585 --> 01:29.381
I’m sure Benji mentioned that
we’re taking him to Chez Luisant tonight.

01:29.381 --> 01:31.925
Well, I was hoping that you could join us.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.427
As a fun surprise for him.

01:33.427 --> 01:35.304
‐ Yeah! Yeah, of course. That'd be great.

01:35.304 --> 01:37.764
‐ Oh, wonderful.
You may want to dress up a bit.

01:37.764 --> 01:40.601
But don’t worry, it isn't, um,
hoity‐toity. It's more, um,

01:40.601 --> 01:42.144
cozy chic.

01:43.103 --> 01:46.815
Mmm. Oh, I'm gonna take a rain check
on the latte.

01:46.815 --> 01:50.736
My, uh, my matcha's just kicked in
and I'm feeling a little buzzy.

01:50.736 --> 01:53.071
I can't wait to celebrate you later.

01:53.071 --> 01:55.282
Bye, Victor.
VICTOR: Bye.

01:55.282 --> 01:57.367
‐ Did my mom just wink at you?

01:57.367 --> 02:00.329
‐ That's how you pay your respects
to "the softest cheeks in Creekwood."

02:00.329 --> 02:04.291
‐ Softest, huh? Let me see.
‐ [laughing] Hey! Come here.

02:04.708 --> 02:07.252
‐ ♪ Somebody to tell me
it'll be all right ♪

02:07.252 --> 02:10.172
♪ Somebody to tell me
it'll be just fine ♪

02:10.172 --> 02:13.467
♪ If someone has been there before,
say it right now ♪

02:13.467 --> 02:15.802
♪ 'Cause I just need to hear it ♪

02:18.263 --> 02:21.850
♪

02:21.850 --> 02:23.644
‐ This is nice.

02:23.644 --> 02:26.063
‐ Yeah, it's fine.
[keyboard keys clicking]

02:26.063 --> 02:29.608
Is it me or does it feel like
we have a very emotional chaperone?

02:31.109 --> 02:32.736
MIA:
Give her a break.

02:32.736 --> 02:35.489
Felix still won’t talk to her.
She’s a mess.

02:35.489 --> 02:37.407
I mean, she's not even wearing heels.

02:37.407 --> 02:40.619
Her motto is usually
“give me three inches or give me death.”

02:40.619 --> 02:44.456
‐ So Felix just barely made the cut.
Ho‐ho!

02:44.456 --> 02:48.001
‐ [sighs] Okay. Andrew...

02:48.001 --> 02:51.839
If Mia accidentally got your mom
committed to a 72‐hour psych hold,

02:51.839 --> 02:54.174
which of these surprise dates
would make you forgive her:

02:54.174 --> 02:56.927
a visit to the Jimmy Carter
Presidential Library,

02:56.927 --> 03:00.347
or a visit to the
Center for Puppetry Arts. Be honest.

03:00.347 --> 03:02.391
‐ These are real places?

03:02.391 --> 03:04.351
God, Atlanta sucks.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.603
‐ [sighs] Guys, this is serious.

03:06.603 --> 03:08.272
I‐I really have to think of
something amazing

03:08.272 --> 03:09.815
to remind Felix
how much I love him!

03:09.815 --> 03:12.401
‐ Lake. [grunts] Breathe.

03:12.401 --> 03:14.111
[exhales]

03:14.111 --> 03:16.989
I’ll help you find
the perfect thing. Okay?

03:16.989 --> 03:19.575
‐ Thank you.

03:19.575 --> 03:22.661
Okay. Now I’m gonna go order us
a bunch of Chinese takeout,

03:22.661 --> 03:24.705
like they do in movies where the lawyers
have to stay up all night

03:24.705 --> 03:27.583
cracking the case. Okay? [sighs]

03:29.668 --> 03:31.962
‐ I thought we were gonna order pizza.

03:31.962 --> 03:36.466
‐ I know. I just need to be here
for Lake, is all.

03:36.466 --> 03:39.178
Look, if we finish early,

03:39.178 --> 03:43.140
we can order pizza from the
comfort of my bedroom.

03:45.142 --> 03:48.145
LAKE:
Oh, uh, can you hold on for a second?

03:48.145 --> 03:50.314
Guys. Guys!

03:50.314 --> 03:52.191
Smash on your own time, okay?

03:52.191 --> 03:54.193
A relationship hangs in the balance.

03:56.904 --> 03:58.739
‐ Betrayed by my lover.

03:59.907 --> 04:03.744
They took away my mother.
Will I ever recover?

04:03.744 --> 04:06.330
‐ Uh, hey, Felix.

04:06.330 --> 04:08.916
When was the last time you took a shower?

04:08.916 --> 04:11.418
RAHIM: Yeah, you're really making me
regret having a nose.
[Felix sniffs]

04:11.418 --> 04:13.504
My nose is my second favorite body part.

04:15.255 --> 04:16.882
Wouldn't you like to know?

04:16.882 --> 04:19.968
‐ All right. I'll go.

04:25.057 --> 04:27.434
‐ Hey, would you guys be able to
keep an eye on him tonight?

04:27.434 --> 04:30.229
Benji’s mom invited me to
Chez Luisant for his birthday.

04:30.229 --> 04:32.773
‐ I heard J. Lo ate there every night
while she was staying here

04:32.773 --> 04:34.566
filming that new movie
about being a scrappy mom

04:34.566 --> 04:35.651
finding true love.

04:35.651 --> 04:37.110
‐ Hasn't she already made that movie?
[shower facet turns, water runs]

04:37.110 --> 04:39.446
‐ Oh, and every Avengers movie
is uniquely different.

04:41.073 --> 04:43.450
You're not actually
gonna wear that, are you?

04:43.450 --> 04:46.745
‐ Uh, yeah.
Benji’s mom said it’s "cozy meets chic."

04:46.745 --> 04:50.666
‐ Are you sure you’re gay? I‐‐
I wash my hands of this. Ugh.

04:50.666 --> 04:53.377
‐ Okay, don't‐‐ don't mind her.
We'll find you something to wear.

04:53.377 --> 04:55.337
Something clean and classic.

04:55.337 --> 04:56.797
You know‐‐

04:56.797 --> 05:00.050
Okay, wow. You, you really love
the non‐descript athletic tee.

05:00.050 --> 05:02.636
‐ Uh, well I could probably borrow
one of my dad's button‐ups.

05:02.636 --> 05:04.805
Uh, you know, he, he's a little bit
bigger than I am,

05:04.805 --> 05:06.974
but I could tuck it in.
‐ We're probably the same size, right?

05:06.974 --> 05:08.767
‐ Oh, no, no, no.
It's, it's okay. Really‐‐

05:08.767 --> 05:09.935
‐ It's fine.

05:11.728 --> 05:15.399
And it's, uh,
it's last season St. Laurent, so...

05:15.399 --> 05:17.234
try not to spill anything on it.

05:17.234 --> 05:20.404
‐ Well, uh, try not to spill
anything on this, either,

05:20.404 --> 05:22.906
because it is present day Old Navy.

05:24.408 --> 05:26.368
‐ Cute.
[laughs]

05:27.035 --> 05:29.079
Just... yeah.

05:29.955 --> 05:31.331
‐ All right.
[laughs]

05:31.331 --> 05:34.960
Oh, damn, Victor! Lookin' good.

05:34.960 --> 05:37.546
That will be the first and last
time I ever catcall my brother.

05:37.546 --> 05:40.340
[laughs]
‐ Hey, guys, there's snacks
in the kitchen.

05:40.340 --> 05:43.552
Rahim, Keto friendly. I got you.
‐ Oh.

05:44.469 --> 05:47.806
‐ [gasps] Mira que handsome.

05:47.806 --> 05:49.474
[Isabel giggles]

05:49.474 --> 05:53.312
Hold on. Your collar is all crooked.

05:53.312 --> 05:54.730
There.

05:54.730 --> 05:56.440
So guess where I'm going tonight.

05:57.691 --> 06:00.986
My first PFLAG meeting.

06:00.986 --> 06:02.613
‐ Really?
‐ Yeah.

06:02.613 --> 06:06.783
I need a little advice
on how to talk to Adrian about...

06:06.783 --> 06:08.202
who you are.

06:09.453 --> 06:10.704
‐ Thank you.

06:11.538 --> 06:15.876
‐ Thank you for being so patient with me.

06:18.545 --> 06:20.214
‐ You guys are out of towels.

06:23.759 --> 06:25.636
[indistinct chatter]

06:25.636 --> 06:27.888
CHARLES:
It was so good meeting you.

06:27.888 --> 06:30.766
‐ Well, look who the cat dragged in.

06:30.766 --> 06:33.352
CHARLES:
And what a dapper cat he is.

06:33.352 --> 06:36.021
Wait, Victor isn’t the cat.
He’s what the cat is dragging.

06:36.021 --> 06:37.689
That is such a strange expression.

06:37.689 --> 06:39.983
‐ Victor, what are you doing here?

06:39.983 --> 06:42.861
‐ Uh, good to see you, too.

06:42.861 --> 06:45.656
‐ No, sorry, I‐I just meant‐‐
‐ We asked Victor to join us

06:45.656 --> 06:47.199
as a little birthday surprise.

06:47.199 --> 06:48.784
VICTOR:
Ah, well, you guys look great.

06:48.784 --> 06:53.205
I wasn’t totally sure what “cozy chic”
meant, but now I think I get it.

06:53.205 --> 06:56.166
‐ It sounds like my wife gave you
one of her indecipherable dress codes.

06:56.166 --> 06:58.877
Last week, it was
“fireside fashionable.“

06:58.877 --> 07:00.587
MARGARET:
Well, no matter what I say,

07:00.587 --> 07:02.923
he always wears the same sweater vest.

07:02.923 --> 07:04.174
[Victor chuckles]

07:04.174 --> 07:05.634
‐ Oh, there's our table.

07:05.634 --> 07:07.636
‐ Oh, Victor, you are in for a treat.

07:07.636 --> 07:10.514
The food here is truly divine.
[laughs]

07:15.394 --> 07:18.522
♪

07:21.525 --> 07:23.527
[keyboard keys clicking]
LAKE: Any other ideas?

07:24.570 --> 07:27.823
‐ Ponce City Market has rooftop
ice skating.

07:27.823 --> 07:30.284
‐ Oof, no. Felix doesn't like ice skating.

07:30.284 --> 07:33.787
He thinks it’s a recipe for disaster
to wear weapons as shoes.

07:36.290 --> 07:39.710
Oh, my God! The aquarium has
a deep sea fish exhibit.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.044
‐ Okay.

07:41.044 --> 07:44.256
‐ Oh, uh, Felix taught me about this

07:44.256 --> 07:46.550
weird glow‐in‐the‐dark deep sea fish

07:46.550 --> 07:49.553
the very first time we kissed,
and it's kind of our origin story.

07:49.553 --> 07:51.305
He would love this.

07:51.305 --> 07:54.433
‐ All right. Aquarium it is.

07:56.852 --> 07:58.395
‐ What's the look?

07:59.980 --> 08:03.317
I just...
Okay, are you sure this is the right move?

08:03.317 --> 08:08.530
I mean, Felix has a pretty
good reason to be upset.

08:08.530 --> 08:14.411
And maybe what he needs more than a fancy
aquarium date is just...

08:14.411 --> 08:15.829
time.

08:17.539 --> 08:19.124
‐ Yeah, but what do you mean

08:19.124 --> 08:21.835
he has a pretty good reason to be upset?

08:21.835 --> 08:25.047
Mia, I was trying to help him.
‐ I know that.

08:25.047 --> 08:29.843
But he asked you not to say anything
about his mom, Lake. And you did.

08:29.843 --> 08:32.804
And now she’s being
detained at a hospital.

08:32.804 --> 08:35.557
‐ 'Cause she's sick, and she needs help.

08:35.557 --> 08:38.769
‐ I’m just saying Felix trusted you,

08:38.769 --> 08:41.813
and you betrayed that trust.

08:41.813 --> 08:45.734
I know what it's like
to have a mom go away.

08:45.734 --> 08:49.905
And it hurts.
‐ I know it hurts.

08:49.905 --> 08:52.533
Because I was there for you
when it happened.

08:52.533 --> 08:54.451
Holding your hand and being your friend.

08:54.451 --> 08:58.121
Which is clearly something
you can’t be for me right now. So...

08:58.121 --> 09:02.292
‐ Lake, come on.
‐ No. No, uh, thanks‐‐
thanks for the support.

09:02.292 --> 09:06.338
Now I just gotta figure out how to make
an aquarium romantic AF.

09:11.677 --> 09:15.556
‐ And I think‐‐ Let’s put in an order
of le ratatouille

09:15.556 --> 09:16.932
for the table.
SERVER: Great choice.

09:16.932 --> 09:18.141
‐ Thank you, Henri.

09:18.141 --> 09:19.810
‐ Your mom really does say ratatouille

09:19.810 --> 09:21.937
like she's trying to win a Michelin star.
[chuckles]

09:21.937 --> 09:23.063
[clinking on glass]

09:23.063 --> 09:25.649
‐ Uh, Mom, can I actually
talk to you for a second?

09:25.649 --> 09:29.278
‐ Sure. Right after the
sparkling cider toast.

09:29.278 --> 09:33.323
Benjamin, we couldn't love you more.

09:33.323 --> 09:36.410
We all know that the last couple of years
haven't been easy‐‐

09:36.410 --> 09:38.287
‐ Mom, I, I just‐‐
‐ Let her have her moment.

09:38.287 --> 09:39.913
She practiced this at home for an hour.

09:39.913 --> 09:43.250
A very long hour.
‐ Shush!

09:45.377 --> 09:48.213
After your car accident last year,

09:48.213 --> 09:49.882
you were so hard on yourself,

09:49.882 --> 09:52.259
and things were...

09:52.259 --> 09:54.928
pretty dark for a while there, and...

09:54.928 --> 09:57.014
you decided to put in the hard work.

09:57.014 --> 10:00.350
Look at you now.
You're so committed to your...

10:00.350 --> 10:04.313
your sobriety, and your AA meetings.

10:04.313 --> 10:07.900
And last week,
you earned your one‐year chip.

10:07.900 --> 10:10.944
We couldn’t possibly be
prouder of you, darling.

10:10.944 --> 10:13.363
We love you so much, Benji.

10:13.363 --> 10:15.949
Happy birthday, sweetheart.

10:15.949 --> 10:18.577
‐ Wait, wait. You're, you're sober?

10:18.577 --> 10:20.454
‐ I have to go to the bathroom.

10:24.333 --> 10:26.210
‐ Did you not know?

10:26.210 --> 10:29.379
‐ I, I knew about the accident,
but I didn't know that he was in AA.

10:37.429 --> 10:38.722
[phone chimes, vibrates]

10:46.438 --> 10:48.065
[cartoon chatters over phone]
[Felix sighs]

10:48.065 --> 10:49.566
[bubbling]

10:52.110 --> 10:55.447
‐ Hey, buddy. We’re having a J. Lo
movie marathon,

10:55.447 --> 10:57.241
because apparently
if someone mentions J. Lo,

10:57.241 --> 11:00.035
Rahim has to have a marathon.
Wanna join?

11:01.078 --> 11:04.081
[phone vibrates]
‐ Oh, my God, uh, no. This is, um‐‐

11:04.081 --> 11:06.416
This is my mom's social worker. Um...

11:08.919 --> 11:11.296
Hi, Alison. Uh, what's up?

11:17.886 --> 11:19.888
Okay, the doctor thought‐‐

11:21.807 --> 11:22.933
I understand.

11:24.476 --> 11:26.645
Yeah, uh, can, can I have a second?

11:29.314 --> 11:33.569
Um, based on evaluations,

11:33.569 --> 11:36.405
they are doing an extended hold.

11:37.447 --> 11:40.284
It can, uh, it can,
it can be up to 14 days.

11:45.706 --> 11:47.708
Hi. Yeah, sorry about that.

11:47.708 --> 11:50.669
‐ This sucks, I mean,
no one deserves this less than Felix.

11:50.669 --> 11:53.422
He's literally the sweatiest person.

11:53.422 --> 11:56.133
‐ No, you were about to say sweetest.

11:56.133 --> 11:58.177
Looks like someone has a little crush.

11:58.177 --> 12:00.429
‐ On Felix? Yeah. Right.

12:00.429 --> 12:02.806
He's like a sweet, goofy Muppet.

12:02.806 --> 12:04.433
Humph.
♪ rap music playing over TV ♪

12:04.433 --> 12:07.227
‐ I got bored waiting for you guys,
so I started Hustlers.

12:07.227 --> 12:08.604
♪ rap music continues ♪

12:08.604 --> 12:11.732
Two questions: What’s a lap dance,
and why is it so expensive?

12:12.691 --> 12:13.609
‐ Um...

12:14.818 --> 12:17.279
SHELBY: Hi, everyone. This week's meeting
will be starting in a few minutes.

12:17.279 --> 12:19.948
‐ Thank you.
SHELBY: Now, y'all grab a snack
and take a seat.

12:24.745 --> 12:26.246
‐ Hey.
‐ Hey, you.

12:26.246 --> 12:29.249
I know. One creamer,
three Splendas. Right?

12:29.249 --> 12:30.959
‐ You remembered.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.212
Ah, bless you.
[both chuckle]

12:33.212 --> 12:36.590
‐ Well...
‐ Lord knows I could use the caffeine.

12:36.590 --> 12:40.344
Zoey kept me up watching
another Kristen Stewart movie.

12:40.344 --> 12:44.473
I swear, my kid is obsessed
with that fidgety woman.

12:44.473 --> 12:47.351
Kind of like you. [laughs]
‐ Oh, stop.

12:47.351 --> 12:48.894
After you...

12:50.229 --> 12:54.942
♪

13:05.202 --> 13:07.579
‐ Hey.
‐ Hey.

13:09.122 --> 13:12.918
I'm really sorry you had to
find out about AA like that.

13:12.918 --> 13:15.045
What about at the cabin?

13:15.045 --> 13:19.466
We, we were drinking vodka.
‐ I was drinking orange juice.

13:19.466 --> 13:23.595
I switched out my cup
when no one was looking.

13:23.595 --> 13:27.015
Whenever we’re around
alcohol, I, I just... fake it.

13:27.015 --> 13:30.060
It’s easier for me to pretend that I drink

13:30.060 --> 13:32.271
instead of explain why I don’t.

13:32.271 --> 13:34.606
‐ I mean, I, I get that. I do.

13:34.606 --> 13:36.608
With other people.

13:38.110 --> 13:41.697
But why didn't you tell me that?
We tell each other everything.

13:41.697 --> 13:44.324
‐ I don't know, Victor.
I, I guess I just...

13:44.324 --> 13:48.161
didn't want you to think of me as
your boyfriend, the alcoholic.

13:49.496 --> 13:51.248
‐ I would never judge you like that.

13:51.248 --> 13:53.500
‐ No, of course not.

13:53.500 --> 13:56.378
It’s just my own stuff. Look, can you...

13:56.378 --> 14:00.215
[sighs] I’m sorry, okay.
Can, can you just forgive me?

14:04.178 --> 14:05.762
‐ I want to.

14:08.056 --> 14:13.187
It's just that you always push me
to be more open with you.

14:14.563 --> 14:18.233
And this is like, a huge part of
your life that you just hid from me.

14:22.196 --> 14:25.657
‐ You know, you could at least try and be
a little more understanding.

14:25.657 --> 14:28.744
[scoffs] I’ve put up with
a ton of your shit,

14:28.744 --> 14:30.412
and never made you feel bad
about any of it.
‐ Whoa‐‐

14:30.412 --> 14:34.041
What is that supposed to mean?
‐ Oh, nothing. You know, just forget it.

14:34.041 --> 14:37.252
‐ No, please, tell me. What shit
have you had to put up with?

14:38.253 --> 14:40.214
‐ I don't know, Victor.

14:40.214 --> 14:43.342
There’s the fact that you’re
completely new to being gay.

14:43.342 --> 14:47.095
And every single thing that we go through
is this massively big deal

14:47.095 --> 14:48.931
that we have to examine.

14:48.931 --> 14:51.016
And then, then there's your mom,

14:51.016 --> 14:53.268
who thinks that you’re going to Hell
for being with me.

14:53.268 --> 14:55.812
And every time she takes
a tiny step forward,

14:55.812 --> 14:58.190
I’m supposed to jump for joy.

14:58.190 --> 15:01.568
I mean, I, I'm not even allowed
in your house.

15:01.568 --> 15:04.363
But do I ever make you feel guilty
about any of that stuff?

15:04.363 --> 15:08.116
No. No, I've been nothing but patient,
and, and understanding.

15:08.116 --> 15:10.827
The very least you could do is just,
is return the favor.

15:14.206 --> 15:16.542
